author: Falk Alexander
commit_message:
Strip out non-ASCII characters on decrypt (#97)

Non-ASCII characters need to be removed from the string, otherwise LXML will throw a ValueError exception because the string contains non-ASCII, non-UTF8 or control characters, which are not allowed in valid XML.
Decoding in UTF8 doesn't remove this characters so it's needed to remove them manually.

commit_message:
Support for field references. (#178)

* Remove unused imports. Fix some pep8 warnings.

* Group imports by standard library, third party, application.

* Add support for field references:
- deref() for replacing/formatting a field reference in given value. Available through PyKeePass, Entry and Group.
- ref() for creating a reference to given attribute of current Entry or Group.

* Fix most pep8 warnings in tests.py.

* Use UUID instances for compatibility with uuid changes in https://github.com/libkeepass/pykeepass/commit/616a23f7889a1c5274c2479bc4c714b1fb084c3b
Move BaseElement.deref() and BaseElement.ref() to Entry, field references aren't supported for groups in KeePass.

* Add tests for field references.
